Rating: 4
I modified this recipe a bit by adding the following: about 1/4 C ketchup and 2 Tbsp.brown sugar plus extra chili powder and paprika for more spice/heat. I also add a dash of liquid smoke and a dash of Worchestershire sauce. I shredded all the vegetables in my food processor and it made this an easy meal that can be frozen.

Rating: 4
Made tiny cubes out of the veggies instead...I hate grating. Cooked down perfectly, added a nice, light crunch. My old man said it was the best sloppy joes he'd had in years. The recipe is solid, so you can definitely add spices, etc. to taste. Probably could throw in some peppers too.

Rating: 4
Great sloppy joes with the added benefit of being healthy. The first time I made it I made it with beef and it turned out better than with the turkey. But, either way it is great. I used zucchini instead of summer squash and minced all the veggies pretty small so they cooked down. Plus I added a T of brown sugar and a little ground red pepper/cayenne for a little extra flavor and spice. My son, husband and I loved it.

